args:
Tartarus appears and bars the way as the party
rushes to the Sacred Tree. Cleo is shaken when
Tartarus asserts there is no replacement for
Alberius and none who will inherit his will,
and the party then readies for battle.
This is as far I shall see you.\nContinue ahead on this road.
The way to the Sacred Tree should be in\nNotte's mind, so I don't suspect you will\nlose your way.
Yep, it's in there clear as day!
I beseech you all: Stop Nedrick.\nAnd stop my son.
And thank you again, Finlorda. You told\nme everything, and because of that, I now\nunderstand how to proceed forward.
I pray you meet no hardship on the way.
Forgive me for doing so, but I again leave\ntheir safekeeping in your hands, Gatov.
Be careful, old friend. Be very careful.
I've got a nasty feeling about this entire\nbusiness; someone's clearly attempting\nto sow mayhem in the Faerie Kingdom.
Agreed. And once the situation is settled,\nI will head straight for the Sacred Tree.\nOh, and Gatov?
Keep what we discussed last night\nclose to your heart—always.
Understood. Until next time, be well.
I know we're moving at a brisk pace,\nbut is everyone all right so far?
We are well, Brother. Let us hurry.
I wish we could take the Gran Fiore instead\nof our own two feet, but I fear she is most\nill-equipped for such a steep path.
Somethin' up, Gatov? You've been givin'\nour surroundings the stink eye for hours.
Take weapons in hand, everyone.\nSomething wicked walks with us.
Unknown signature detected.\n▷It's true. Someone's close!◁
All of you appear utterly unchanged.
Tartarus! What are you doing here?
Stand aside, Tartarus. We've no time\nto trade words or blows with you today.
So the fabricated doll makes his way\nto the Sacred Tree.
I assume Finlorda revealed the truth of\nyour fell birth to you by now?

You thought yourself royal—human, even.
But this was always the basest of lies;
you are naught but a doll made from the
Other.
Who I am is of no consequence right now.\nI want to know my father's thoughts,\nand I need to save Zethia.
And I also have to stop\nNedrick and Jinlorda.

Even now, you cannot break free of the
vainglories of the king's descendants.
Perhaps this is proof enough of the
Wise King's greatness.
The king was supreme. Peerless.\nUnparalleled in his transcendence.
You are a sad little man who cloaks\nhimself in the name of this great hero,\nand for that you deserve death!
It doesn't matter who or what he is!\n{player_name} is the one who\ninherits His Majesty's will!
Inherits his will? Aaaah ha ha ha!
The king's will belonged to him alone.\nAnd when he died, it perished with him.
You trust in this pathetic creature because\nyou now lack His Majesty's guidance.
Before this world which saw fit to sacrifice\nHis Majesty meets its ruin, you will both\nsuffer the hammer of judgment.
We've got a fight on our hands.\nGet ready, everyone!
Indeed, we are the jaws of destruction\nleft unto this world.
O king, be my aegis! I offer these souls\nunto yours as oblation!
